      "content": "but i've already changed all my passwords and even used 2FA... nothing changed. the thing is, the posts aren't just random stuff, they feel like an extension of my actual thoughts. like, if i were to post something tomorrow, it would probably be exactly what this \"thing\" is posting now. it feels less like someone is hacking me and more like my digital self has just... survived me, or been detached. like the real me isn't the one controlling my accounts anymore. doesn't that sound terrifying? like how could an AI be that precise?",
